3) Reading from Your PokemonNFT Contract
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
With the wagmi config set up, let’s add a hook or utility function that returns a wagmi contract instance pointed at your deployed PokemonNFT. We just need its ABI and deployed address:

• Grab the ABI (application binary interface) from your artifacts (or define a minimal subset of read/write functions).  
• Recall that our PokemonNFT is deployed at the address from the Hardhat Ignition module or from your logs.  

Create a file: wagmi/usePokemonNft.ts

import { useContractRead, useContractWrite, usePrepareContractWrite } from 'wagmi';
import PokemonNftAbi from '../abi/PokemonNFT.json';

const POKEMON_NFT_ADDRESS = '<Your-Deployed-Address>';  // e.g. 0x...

export function usePokemonNftReads(tokenId: number) {
  // Example: read card metadata
  const { data: cardMetadata, isLoading: isCardMetadataLoading } = useContractRead({
    address: POKEMON_NFT_ADDRESS,
    abi: PokemonNftAbi,
    functionName: 'getCardMetadata',
    args: [tokenId],
    watch: true
  });

  return {
    cardMetadata,
    isCardMetadataLoading
  };
}

Then in your Home page (app/page.tsx), you might do:

