4) Admin Mint Page (Basic Admin Functionality)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Your marketplace or admin might want a page to “Mint Rare Card”. Since only MINTER_ROLE addresses can call mintRareCard, we’ll provide an interface to do so. The user can supply relevant fields (name, hp, etc.), then the contract call is triggered. Let’s scaffold a page at app/mint/page.tsx:

'use client';

import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { useContractWrite, usePrepareContractWrite } from 'wagmi';
import PokemonNftAbi from '../../abi/PokemonNFT.json';

const POKEMON_NFT_ADDRESS = '<Your-Deployed-Address>';

export default function MintPage() {
  const [name, setName] = useState('');
  const [hp, setHp] = useState('100');
  const [cardType, setCardType] = useState('0');       // e.g. 0 = Fire?
  const [rarity, setRarity] = useState('0');           // e.g. 0 = Common
  const [cardDetailURL, setCardDetailURL] = useState('');

  // Prepare the contract call
  // mintRareCard(address to, CardMetadata data, string tokenURI_) 
  const { config } = usePrepareContractWrite({
    address: POKEMON_NFT_ADDRESS,
    abi: PokemonNftAbi,
    functionName: 'mintRareCard',
    args: [
      // For demonstration, we can mint to ourselves:
      undefined, // We'll fill in from the connected wallet below or from an input
      {
        name: name,
        cardType: Number(cardType),
        rarity: Number(rarity),
        cardDetailURL,
        hp: Number(hp),
      },
      '' // an empty string if you have no off-chain metadata URI
    ]
  });

  const { write, isLoading, isSuccess } = useContractWrite(config);

  // Example: a simple form
  return (
    <div className="p-4">
      <h2>Mint Rare Card (Admin Only)</h2>
      <div className="space-y-2 mt-4">
        <div>
          <label>Name</label>
          <input
            className="border ml-2"
            value={name}
            onChange={(e) => setName(e.target.value)}
          />
        </div>

        <div>
          <label>HP</label>
          <input
            className="border ml-2"
            type="number"
            value={hp}
            onChange={(e) => setHp(e.target.value)}
          />
        </div>

        <div>
          <label>Card Type Index</label>
          <input
            className="border ml-2"
            type="number"
            value={cardType}
            onChange={(e) => setCardType(e.target.value)}
          />
        </div>

        <div>
          <label>Rarity Index (0=Common..5=SecretRare)</label>
          <input
            className="border ml-2"
            type="number"
            value={rarity}
            onChange={(e) => setRarity(e.target.value)}
          />
        </div>

        <div>
          <label>Card Detail URL</label>
          <input
            className="border ml-2"
            value={cardDetailURL}
            onChange={(e) => setCardDetailURL(e.target.value)}
          />
        </div>

        <button
          className="border px-4 py-2"
          disabled={!write || isLoading}
          onClick={() => write?.()}
        >
          Mint
        </button>
        {isSuccess && <p>Mint successful!</p>}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

Of course, you’ll only succeed if the connected wallet has the MINTER_ROLE or if the address is the default admin. If it fails on-chain, you’ll see a revert message.

